President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the state of North Carolina due to severe storms, tornadoes, and flooding that occurred from February 6 to February 19, 2020. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Elizabeth Turner has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by the state and based on damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.